            <h2>5 Commandments</h2>

            <h3 style="padding-top: 15px">Always</h3>
            <p>This is the most important thing a person has to do to live by your ideals. If someone ever experiences doubt, they should be able to look to this to center themselves.</p>
            <p>
                Examples: Always...
                <ul>
                    <li>Ease suffering where you find it.</li>
                    <li>Search for truth where it could be hidden.</li>
                    <li> Trust your instincts to guide you.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <input name="flags.detailedcharinfo.always" value="{{flags.detailedcharinfo.always}}" id="always" type="text" maxlength="300" placeholder="eg. I always trust my gut when i'm in a bad spot, it's gotten me out of them more than once" />

            <br />
            <h3 style="padding-top: 15px">Never</h3>
            <p>The commandment is designed to prevent people from losing their way. It forbids an activity or way of thinking that you believe could lead them down a harmful path.</p>
            <p>
                Examples: Never...
                <ul>
                    <li>Trust a person whose only achievement is wealth.</li>
                    <li>Trade freedom for safety. </li>
                    <li>Kill for something you cannot hold.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <input name="flags.detailedcharinfo.never" value="{{flags.detailedcharinfo.never}}" id="never" type="text" maxlength="300" placeholder="eg. Wealth can corrupt your view on the world and people,, don't trust the money nor the people'" />

            <br />
            <h3 style="padding-top: 15px">Sacred</h3>
            <p>There is a place, concept, or thing that you believe holds divine importance.It should be something your followers are encouraged to seek out and protect.</p>
            <p>
                Examples: Sacred...
                <ul>
                    <li>Freedom</li>
                    <li>Forest </li>
                    <li>Music</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <input name="flags.detailedcharinfo.sacred" value="{{flags.detailedcharinfo.sacred}}" id="sacred" type="text" maxlength="300" placeholder="eg. I hold my hymns or home songs highly and they are to never die out" />

            <br />
            <h3 style="padding-top: 15px">Sin</h3>
            <p>There is one crime you believe to be worse than all others. It is something your followers should work to remove from the world&#8212;something that would not be possible in a universe you controlled.</p>
            <p>
                Examples: Sin..
                <ul>
                    <li>Theft</li>
                    <li>Dark magic</li>
                    <li>Harming a child</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <input name="flags.detailedcharinfo.sin" value="{{flags.detailedcharinfo.sin}}" id="sin" type="text" maxlength="300" placeholder="eg. Dark magic results in cursed, death and hatred this sin is unforgivable" />

            <br />
            <h3 style="padding-top: 15px">Self</h3>
            <p>The final commandment is to define a follower's relationship with oneself If someone is to live by your example. how are they to treat themselves?</p>
            <p>
                Examples: Self...
                <ul>
                    <li>Sacrifice is the key to righteousness.</li>
                    <li>Care for yourself so you may care for others.</li>
                    <li>All for one. one for all.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <input name="flags.detailedcharinfo.self" value="{{flags.detailedcharinfo.self}}" id="self" type="text" maxlength="300" placeholder="eg. If you do not care for yourself, then how will you have the strength to care for others" />

        </div>

